                  "narrative": "The threads converge. The cipher is not merely a calling card \u2014 it is a key. Someone has been encoding meeting times and locations in plain sight, using the symbols of the Hermetic Order of the Grey Dawn as a private postal system. The question is whether the murders are the message, or merely the postage. Two paths present themselves: the printshop on Dorset Street, where the typeface may betray the note's origin, and Professor Vane's townhouse in Bloomsbury, where the Order's symbols may yield their meaning.",
