                  "id": "wc-act2-printshop-success",
                  "act": 2,
                  "narrative": "Mott breaks. The words come out in a rush: a man came to him three weeks ago, paid in gold sovereigns, and commissioned a run of cipher notes using a typeface Mott had imported from Frankfurt. The man wore a good coat and spoke like a gentleman. He gave no name, but he left a forwarding address \u2014 a cellar on Dorset Street, two doors down. 'I didn't know what they were for,' Mott says. 'I swear it.' You believe him. That almost makes it worse.",
